---

Identified two issues:

- Wrong theme: `presentation.tex` uses `\usetheme{Madrid}` instead of `\usetheme{TACC16}`. The TACC theme files exist and reference background images.
- Images not loaded: The TACC theme references images in `figures/`, but since the theme isn't used, they aren't loaded.

The log shows no image-loading errors because the theme isn't being used. Updating `presentation.tex` to use the TACC theme:

The TACC theme auto-detects aspect ratio. If Beamer defaults to 16:9, it uses landscape backgrounds. Setting the document class to 4:3 to force portrait:


---

<tool-use data-tool-type="write" data-tool-name="search_replace">

<details><summary>Tool use: **code_edit** • Edit file: /Users/mcawood/Lmod/lmod-main/my_docs/25/sc_25_booth_talk/presentation.tex</summary>

```diff
@@ -4,5 +4,5 @@
  % Location: my_docs/25/sc_25_booth_talk/presentation.tex
  
- \documentclass{beamer}
+ \documentclass[aspectratio=43]{beamer}
  \usetheme{TACC16}
  \usepackage{graphicx}
```

</details>

</tool-use>

---



---


Fixed by explicitly setting the aspect ratio to `43` (4:3 portrait) in the document class. The TACC theme was detecting 16:9 and switching to landscape backgrounds.

With `aspectratio=43`, the theme will:
- Use portrait background images (`master.jpg` for title slide, `secondary.jpg` for content slides)
- Display slides in portrait orientation instead of landscape

Rebuild the PDF to see the change. Slide 2 (and all slides) should now display in portrait mode.
